other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated, measuring up to 8 mm in diameter, with hyperemic walls and is fluid filled, most compatible with acute appendicitis. Lung bases are clear. Imaged heart is not enlarged. No pericardial effusion. Liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenals, kidneys are unremarkable. There is a retroperitoneal lymph node measuring 5 mm in short axis. A few subcentimeter mesenteric lymph nodes noted but do not meet CT criteria for pathologic enlargement. No bowel obstruction.
